import React,{ createContext, useContext, useState } from 'react'

const AuthContent = createContext()


const AuthProvider = (props) => {

  const [auth, setAuth] = useState({
    user:null,
    token:'',
  })

  const [states, setStates] = useState([
    "Andhra Pradesh",
    "Arunachal Pradesh",
    "Assam",
    "Bihar",
    "Chhattisgarh",
    "Goa",
    "Gujarat",
    "Haryana",
    "Himachal Pradesh",
    "Jharkhand",
    "Karnataka",
    "Kerala",
    "Madhya Pradesh",
    "Maharashtra",
    "Manipur",
    "Meghalaya",
    "Mizoram",
    "Nagaland",
    "Odisha",
    "Punjab",
    "Rajasthan",
    "Sikkim",
    "Tamil Nadu",
    "Telangana",
    "Tripura",
    "West Bengal",
    "Uttarakhand",
    "Uttar Pradesh"
])

  const [alert,setAlert] = useState({})
  const [invalid, setInvalid] = useState({})

  return (
    <AuthContent.Provider value={[auth, setAuth, alert, setAlert,invalid, setInvalid ,states]}>
        {props.children}
    </AuthContent.Provider>
  )
}

const useAuth = () => useContext(AuthContent)

export { useAuth, AuthProvider}
